org.apache.flink.cep.nfa

类 NFA<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.cep.nfa.NFA<T>
  • 类型参数:
    T - Type of the processed events
    所有已实现的接口:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class NFA<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Non-deterministic finite automaton implementation.

    The CEP operator keeps one NFA per key, for keyed input streams, and a single global NFA for non-keyed ones. When an event gets processed, it updates the NFA's internal state machine.

    An event that belongs to a partially matched sequence is kept in an internal buffer, which is a memory-optimized data-structure exactly for this purpose. Events in the buffer are removed when all the matched sequences that contain them are:

    1. emitted (success)
    2. discarded (patterns containing NOT)
    3. timed-out (windowed patterns)

    The implementation is strongly based on the paper "Efficient Pattern Matching over Event Streams".

    另请参阅:
    https://people.cs.umass.edu/~yanlei/publications/sase-sigmod08.pdf, 序列化表格

      • process

        public Tuple2<java.util.Collection<java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<T>>>,java.util.Collection<Tuple2<java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<T>>,java.lang.Long>>> process(T event,
                                                                                                                                                                                              long timestamp)
        Processes the next input event. If some of the computations reach a final state then the resulting event sequences are returned. If computations time out and timeout handling is activated, then the timed out event patterns are returned.

        If computations reach a stop state, the path forward is discarded and currently constructed path is returned with the element that resulted in the stop state.

        参数:
        event - The current event to be processed or null if only pruning shall be done
        timestamp - The timestamp of the current event
        返回:
        Tuple of the collection of matched patterns (e.g. the result of computations which have reached a final state) and the collection of timed out patterns (if timeout handling is activated)

        Processes the next input event. If some of the computations reach a final state then the resulting event sequences are returned. If computations time out and timeout handling is activated, then the timed out event patterns are returned.

      • computeNextStates

        private java.util.Collection<ComputationState<T>> computeNextStates(ComputationState<T> computationState,
                                                                    T event,
                                                                    long timestamp)
        Computes the next computation states based on the given computation state, the current event, its timestamp and the internal state machine. The algorithm is:
        1. Decide on valid transitions and number of branching paths. See NFA.OutgoingEdges
        2. Perform transitions:
          1. IGNORE (links in SharedBuffer will still point to the previous event)
            • do not perform for Start State - special case
            • if stays in the same state increase the current stage for future use with number of outgoing edges
            • if after PROCEED increase current stage and add new stage (as we change the state)
            • lock the entry in SharedBuffer as it is needed in the created branch
          2. TAKE (links in SharedBuffer will point to the current event)
            • add entry to the shared buffer with version of the current computation state
            • add stage and then increase with number of takes for the future computation states
            • peek to the next state if it has PROCEED path to a Final State, if true create Final ComputationState to emit results
        3. Handle the Start State, as it always have to remain
        4. Release the corresponding entries in SharedBuffer.
        参数:
        computationState - Current computation state
        event - Current event which is processed
        timestamp - Timestamp of the current event
        返回:
        Collection of computation states which result from the current one
